nodes.text: A Weequay male proprietor worked as a bartender at a cantina in Mos Pelgo. He worked in the bar during the Battle of Endor and still did years after. At one point, he served spotchka to Cobb Vanth, the marshal of the town, and to the Mandalorian bounty hunter Din Djarin, who had come searching for Vanth.

The Weequay, like his fellow inhabitants of Mos Pelgo, regarded Tuskens as brutal enemies. When Djarin proposed an alliance between the townsfolk and the Tuskens, the Weequay shouted that they were monsters.
This Weequay first appeared in Chapter 9 of The Mandalorian and was portrayed by W. Earl Brown.
